le and multiple positionalities that are transnationally distributed. However, paradoxically, they experience a juxtaposition of privilege, integration and separation, which is indicative of the Chinese style of internationalisation. The book adds weight to the argument that China is a temporary destination for foreigners and not one for long-term settlement.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aImmigrantszChinaxSocial conditions. 0aKoreanszChinaxSocial conditions. 0aKoreanszChina. 4aAnthropology. 4aAsian Studies. 4aContemporary Society. 4aEast Asia and North East Asia. 7aEDUCATION / General.2bisacsh  aAnthropology of Migration, South Korean in China, Education and Migration, Structure and agency.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311133235240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048553808?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048553808423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048553808/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-133235-2  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles